tive America.At once timely and personal, Spanos’s meditation acknowledges the priority of being. He emphasizes the dignity not simply of humanity but of all phenomena on the continuum of being, “the groundless ground of any political formation that would claim the name of democracy.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aDemocracyzUnited States. 0aExceptionalismzUnited States. 0aPolitical culturezUnited States. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh1 aPease, Donald E.1 aPease, Donald E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311072902340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823268184zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823268184423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823268184/original  a978-3-11-072902-3  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK